This file must be named .htaccess and placed in the same directory as your index.php and redirect.php files.
Turn on the rewrite engine
Options +FollowSymLinks
RewriteEngine On

Check if the requested file exists. If it does, do not apply the rewrite rule.
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-f
RewriteCond %{REQUEST_FILENAME} !-d

Rewrite any request that doesn't correspond to a real file or directory
to the redirect.php file, passing the last part of the URL as the 'code' parameter.
RewriteRule ^([a-zA-Z0-9]+)$ redirect.php?code=$1 [L,QSA]